news.headline: Veralto reports Q4 sales of $1,345 million, 4.4% increase YoY, with net earnings of $227 million & FY sales increase of 3.4% to $5,193 million with net earnings of $833 million. news.summary: Veralto, a water and product quality solutions company, released its Q4 2024 results with sales growth of 4.4% to $1.345 billion. Full year 2024 sales increased by 3.4% to $5.193 billion. Operating profit margins were 22.9% for Q4 and 23.3% for the full year. Net earnings were $227 million for Q4 and $833 million for the full year. Non-GAAP adjusted net earnings were $238 million for Q4 and $883 million for the full year. The company's operating cash flow was $285 million for Q4 and $875 million for the full year. For 2025, they forecast low-to-mid single digit core sales growth and aim for adjusted earnings per share of $3.60 to $3.70. They plan to discuss these results in an upcoming investor conference call.
